    <div class="container">
        <div class="faq-list">
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What does a title company do?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>A title company researches the history of a property to confirm legal ownership, identifies any liens or claims against it, issues title insurance to protect buyers and lenders from future disputes, and manages the escrow process — holding funds and documents until all closing conditions are met.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What is title insurance and do I need it?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Title insurance protects you from financial loss due to defects in the title that weren't discovered during the title search — things like undisclosed liens, forgery, errors in public records, or unknown heirs. Lenders require a lender's policy; an owner's policy is optional but strongly recommended.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How fast can you deliver a title commitment?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>We typically deliver title commitments within 2 business days. The industry average is 5-7 days. For rush situations, call us directly at {{ site.phone }}.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What is escrow?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Escrow is a neutral third-party arrangement where funds, documents, and instructions are held until all conditions of a real estate transaction are met. As your escrow company, we ensure that money changes hands only when everything is in order.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What areas do you serve?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>We serve the entire state of Utah with primary focus on the Wasatch Front — Salt Lake City, Provo, Ogden, Park City, and surrounding communities. Mobile closings are available statewide.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What is a mobile closing?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>A mobile closing means we send a licensed escrow officer to the location of your choice — a real estate office, the buyer's home, a hospital, or anywhere convenient. Same professional service, flexible location.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you handle commercial transactions?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We handle commercial title and escrow including multi-parcel deals, 1031 exchanges, construction escrow, and entity closings. Our team has extensive experience with complex commercial files.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you offer volume pricing?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We offer competitive volume pricing for real estate agents, brokers, and lenders who consistently send business our way. Contact us to discuss a volume arrangement.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How do I send you a new order?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Email us at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>, call <a href="tel:{{ site.phone }}">{{ site.phone }}</a>, or use our <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>. Send the purchase contract and we'll take it from there. We confirm receipt within 1 business hour.</p></div></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What do I need to bring to closing?</summary><div class="faq-answer"><p>Bring a valid government-issued photo ID (driver's license or passport). If funds are required, we'll provide wiring instructions in advance — we do not accept personal checks for closing funds over $1,000.</p></div></details>
